{{also|fabian|Fabián}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From the {{etyl|la}} {{term|Fabianus|lang=la}}, belonging to [[Fabius]], a Roman family name (borne by a general who won by avoiding decisive contests), possibly derived from {{term|faba||bean|lang=la}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Advocating that [[socialism]] be reached through a series of gradual and moderate reforms; believing in the slogan, ''The movement is everything, the goal is nothing''; relating to the Fabian Society, a British socialist society advocating [[reformist]] [[socialism]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A fabian [[socialist]], a [[gradualist]] socialist; a member of the Fabian Society.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|gradualist socialist}} [[gradualist]], [[reformist]], [[social democrat]]

====Related terms====
